A total of 719 Chinese DS probands from 2005 and later were collected from the child neurology units of Peking University First Hospital. Sanger sequencing, panel NGS sequencing and MLPA identified 591 (82% of 719) of the probands as carrying potentially pathogenic SCN1A mutations (rare missense, nonsense, frame-shift, and splice site mutations)20,21,59,44. All probands fulfilled the following criteria and were diagnosed with DS21,43,44,48,67: (a) seizure onset within 12 months of birth (average age of onset of 5.17 months, 95% CI 5.17 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
